comment.narrative:
BIOFIN Phase II will continue to build on the results achieved in Phase I: 
-	The BIOFIN Methodology is tested and available with guidance, case studies and lessons learned in BIOFIN Phase I; 
-	BIOFIN assessments are in place in 30 countries providing information, analysis and recommendations on the existing policies and institutions, biodiversity expenditure and financial gap data along with the prioritized financial needs at country level; 
-	Biodiversity Finance Plans are in place in 30 countries providing a basis for the prioritization and implementation of finance solutions at country level; 
-	Global and Country teams are in place along with Steering Committees and Technical working groups at country level.

Kazakhstan: 
-

Inception phase:
1) Presentation of the goals and objectives of the 2nd phase of BIOFIN in Kazakhstan to the stakeholders within the framework of the inception workshop and preparation of the inception report;
2) Coordination of intermediate project results with the members of the SC; 

Finance solution 1. Strenghtening PA management planning for improved financing
1) Submission of a draft of the updated Methodology of the Development of Management Plans for PAs for approval to the Forestry and Wildlife Committee;
2) Evaluation of the PAs achievements with current financial planning, assessment of the PA environment and key internal gaps for resource mobilization. Preparation of recommendations for governments to strengthen the funding for PAs.
3) Development of a draft training program on financial planning in PAs;
4) Conducting targeted workshops, meetings.

Finance solution 2. Introduction of biodiversity offsets as a formal instrument in Kazakhstan
1) Preparation of proposals (table of legislative amendments) for the content of the new Environmental Code as related to biodiversity offsets. Participation in the meetings of working groups on the preparation of the new Environmental Code;
2) Baseline survey of stakeholders on assessment of the potential for development and implementation of effective offsets;
3) Developing guidelines on implementation of effective biodiversity offsets in Kazakhstan, following the mitigation hierarchy and drawing lessons from international best practices;
4) Conducting targeted working meetings, consultations with partners to promote the biodiversity offsets mechanism

Finance Solutions 3. Subsidising game breeding to save animal species and develop hunting concessions
1) Formation of the legal framework for subsidizing the game breeding. Creating a subsidy mechanism;
2) Determining the quantitative and qualitative factors, indicators, conditions for game breeding;
3) Preparation of passport and justification at list for one project on game breeding. 

Finance Solution 4: Tax incentives for ecotourism development in Kazakhstan
1) Conducting a comprehensive analysis and research of best practices for ecotourism, the study of successful certification systems of other countries, and preparation of proposals for the development of ecotourism in the country;
2) Conducting targeted round tables, meetings with partners to coordinate legislative proposals.

Finance Solution 5: Attracting carbon offsets from the international market, multinational enterprises operating in the country
1) Identification and portfolio formation of forest carbon projects, with sound calculations of the impact on the conservation of forest biodiversity and the potential for absorption of greenhouse gases;
2) Creating a legal framework for the implementation of forest carbon projects with the participation of foreign investors;
3) Capacity building of stakeholders (forest industry experts involved in the development, implementation, evaluation and monitoring of forest carbon projects) through informational workshops and publications. 

Finance Solutions 6. Establishing an internal Emission Trading System to integrate the mechanisms into the national legal framework
1) Development and approval of a methodology for preparing projects aimed at reducing greenhouse gas emissions through forest ecosystems;
2) Approval of requirements to the companies involved in development and implementation of the projects aimed at reducing greenhouse gas emissions through forest ecosystems;
3) Conducting targeted workshops, meetings;
4) Selection of 1 pilot project to test the mechanism

MId-Year:
Inception phase:
1) An inception workshop was held, an inception report was prepared and presented to the members of the SC;
2) The interim project results were presented to the SC members at two meetings during the year.

Finance solution 1. Enhanced public finance for the Protected Area System
1) A draft of the updated Methodology for PAs was approved by the Forestry and Wildlife Committee;
2) Pecommendations for governments to strengthen the funding for PAs is prepared and send to government bodies;
3) A draft training program on financial planning in PAs was prepared and tested during a targeted training.
4) Targeted workshops were conducted.

Finance solution 2. Introduction of biodiversity offsets as a formal instrument in Kazakhstan
1) Proposals for offset mechanisms were presented in the Ministry of Energy and included into the draft of the new Environmental Code. The project team participates in themeetings of the Ministry and promotes legislative changes;
2) Baseline survey of stakeholders on assessment of the potential for development and implementation of effective offsets conducted;
3) Guidelines on implementation of effective biodiversity offsets in Kazakhstan are prepared and send to the Government bodies;
4) Targeted meetings with the Akimat of the Mangistau region, KazMunaiGas were held to discuss the details of the offset measures for the Kansu project.

Finance Solutions 3. Subsidising game breeding to save animal species and develop hunting concessions
1) Amendments to the Subsidy Rules were prepared, reviewed by the Ministry of Agriculture for approval;
2) The quantitative and qualitative factors, indicators, conditions for game breeding are defined;
3) Passport and justification at list for one project on game breeding is prepared.

Finance Solution 4: Tax incentives for ecotourism development in Kazakhstan
1) A comprehensive analysis of the best practices of ecotourism, certification systems was carried out; proposals on the development of ecotourism in the country were prepared. Recommendations sent to the Government of Kazakhstan;
2) Proposals were prepared for amending tourism legislation, meetings held with partners to coordinate the legislative proposals.

Finance Solution 5: Attracting carbon offsets from the international market, multinational enterprises operating in the country
1) Established the portfolio of carbon projects to attract foreign investment. Projects discussed and agreed upon with stakeholders;
2) Proposals on the improvement of environmental legislation in regard to the export of carbon units were prepared and submitted to the Government of the Republic of Kazakhstan;
3) Targeted meetings allowed intensifying the decision-making on the promotion of finance solution.

Finance Solutions 6. Establishing an internal Emission Trading System to integrate the mechanisms into the national legal framework
1) The guidelines for the development and implementation of projects, methodology for the evaluation of carbon projects are agreed upon with the Ministry of Energy and the Forestry and Wildlife Committee;
2) 1 pilot project was selected for testing.
